s. As a result, fine dust may exist only in the part of the\nGalactic disk far from both the Galactic center and the edge, while coarse dust\ndominates at the Galactic center, at the disk edge, and outside the disk.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Jun 2016 14:31:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-25"}
